    • Method Detail

      • addAlbum

        public AlbumResponse addAlbum(Long accountId,
                     String title,
                     String mediaFilePath,
                     Long assetId,
                     String attachedMediaFilePath,
                     String attachedMediaURL,
                     Boolean coverAssetNullable,
                     Boolean includeCoverInAssetList,
                     Long startDate,
                     Long endDate,
                     List<String> tags,
                     String description,
                     String albumType,
                     Boolean publicRead,
                     Boolean publicWrite,
                     Boolean publicDelete,
                     Boolean publicAdd,
                     Location location,
                     String locationDescription,
                     Enums.Visibility visibility,
                     String appKey,
                     String cellPhone,
                     String fullAddress)
                       throws SirqulException
        Creates a new album.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/add
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        title - the title of the album
        mediaFilePath - the media file path containing the cover image of the album (this will also the image to the album itself)
        assetId - the asset ID to set the album cover image
        attachedMediaFilePath - the attached media file path containing an asset that the "media" file references. Example to upload a video: the "media" file should contain a screen capture of the video, and the "attachedMedia" should be the actual video.
        attachedMediaURL - this can be used if the "attachedMedia" is a link (i.e. a Youtube video, etc)
        coverAssetNullable - determines whether the cover image of the album can be empty, else will use the user's profile picture as the cover image
        includeCoverInAssetList - determines whether the cover image should be added to the album asset list
        startDate - the start date
        endDate - the end date
        tags - the tags
        description - the description of the album
        albumType - a custom field used for aggregation and searching
        publicRead - determines whether the album's participants has read permissions
        publicWrite - determines whether the album's participants has write permissions
        publicDelete - determines whether the album's participants has delete permissions
        publicAdd - determines whether the album's participants has add permissions
        location - the location used to update the album's location
        locationDescription - the location description
        visibility - determines the album's participants (PUBLIC - includes everyone in the system as a potential participant, PRIVATE - only considers people who have been invited as participants)
        appKey - the application key used to identify the application. Maps to "gameType".
        cellPhone - the cell phone number
        fullAddress - the full address
        Returns:
        a AlbumResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

                                     throws SirqulException
        Adds users to album as participants.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/user/add
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        albumId - the album ID
        read - determines whether the users being added have read permissions
        write - determines whether the users being added have write permissions
        delete - determines whether the users being added have delete permissions
        add - determines whether the users being added have add permissions
        connectionIDs - list of connection IDs
        connectionGroupIDs - list of connection group IDs
        includeFriendGroup - determines whether to include all friends as participants
        Returns:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • approveAlbum

        public SirqulResponse approveAlbum(Long accountId,
                          Long albumId,
                          Enums.ApprovalStatus approvalStatus)
                            throws SirqulException
        Sets the approval status of an album. Only an approval status of APPROVED or FEATURED will be returned when searching for public content. Only someone with EXECUTIVE rights or rights to edit the application can approve/feature the content.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/approve
        Parameters:
        accountId - The account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId sent automatically)
        albumId - The ID of the album
        approvalStatus - The approval status to set {PENDING, REJECTED, APPROVED, FEATURED}
        Returns:
        SirqulResponse with success or fail message.
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • searchAlbums

        public AlbumListResponse searchAlbums(Long accountId,
                             Long ownerId,
                             String keyword,
                             List<Enums.Ownership> filters,
                             String albumType,
                             Enums.AlbumApiMap sortField,
                             Boolean descending,
                             Integer start,
                             Integer limit,
                             Long dateCreated,
                             Location location,
                             Double range,
                             String appKey)
                               throws SirqulException
        Searches on albums.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/search
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        ownerId - search on albums that have been created by this account (that the user has permissions to)
        keyword - keyword search string
        filters - the filters, list of Enums.Ownership
        albumType - filter albums with this album type
        sortField - the field to sort by. See Enums.AlbumApiMap
        descending - determines whether the sorted list is in descending or ascending order
        start - the start index for pagination
        limit - the limit for pagination
        dateCreated - filter on items that have been created before this date (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        location - the location used to search around
        range - the range to search
        appKey - the application key. Maps to "gameType".
        Returns:
        a AlbumListResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • searchAlbumsByDistance

        public AlbumListResponse searchAlbumsByDistance(Long accountId,
                                       Long ownerId,
                                       String keyword,
                                       List<Enums.Ownership> filters,
                                       List<String> albumTypes,
                                       Integer start,
                                       Integer limit,
                                       Long dateCreated,
                                       Location location,
                                       Double range,
                                       String appKey)
                                         throws SirqulException
        Searches on albums sorted by proximity (the distance the album is away from the user). The user's current location is required.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/distanceSearch
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        ownerId - search on albums that have been created by this account
        keyword - keyword search string
        filters - list of Enums.Ownership
        albumTypes - filter albums with this album type
        start - the start index for pagination
        limit - the limit for pagination
        dateCreated - filter on items that have been created before this date (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        location - the location of where the search is centered on
        range - the maximum range the album can be from the user
        appKey - the application key. Maps to "gameType".
        Returns:
        AlbumListResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response with error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • updateAlbumNotifications

                                      Long albumId,
                                      Boolean blocked,
                                      Boolean notifications)
                                        throws SirqulException
        Sets whether a user wants to receive or block all notifications from an album (notifications are allowed by default).

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/notifications
        Parameters:
        accountId - the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        albumId - the ID of the album to receive or block notifications
        blocked - sets the album as blocked
        notifications - determines whether the user receives notifications for that album
        Returns:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
